  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legally, it involves concealing the source of money obtained through criminal activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or other illegal means. The specific definition can vary somewhat between jurisdictions, but typically includes three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration - making the money appear legitimate\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering laws?",
